source.stripe.stripe.balance_transaction.name: balance_transaction
source.stripe.stripe.balance_transaction.description: Balance transactions represent funds moving through your Stripe account. They're created for every type of transaction that comes into or flows out of your Stripe account balance.

amount.name: amount
amount.description: Gross amount of the transaction, in cents.

available_on.name: available_on
available_on.description: The date the transaction’s net funds will become available in the Stripe balance.

connected_account_id.name: connected_account_id
connected_account_id.description: The ID of the account connected to the transaction.

created.name: created
created.description: Time at which the record was created. Dates in the requested timezone, or UTC if not provided.

currency.name: currency
currency.description: Three-letter ISO currency code, in lowercase.

description.name: description
description.description: An arbitrary string attached to the object. Often useful for displaying to users.

exchange_rate.name: exchange_rate
exchange_rate.description: The exchange rate used, if applicable, for this transaction. Specifically, if money was converted from currency A to currency B, then the amount in currency A, times exchange_rate, would be the amount in currency B.

fee.name: fee
fee.description: fees (in cents) paid for this transaction.

net.name: net
net.description: Net amount of the transaction, in cents.

reporting_category.name: reporting_category
reporting_category.description: Improves on the type field by providing a more-useful grouping for most finance and reporting purposes.

source.name: source
source.description: The Stripe object to which this transaction is related.

status.name: status
status.description: If the transaction’s net funds are available in the Stripe balance yet. Either 'available' or 'pending'.

type.name: type
type.description: The type of transaction.  Possible values are adjustment, advance, advance_funding, application_fee, application_fee_refund, charge, connect_collection_transfer, issuing_authorization_hold, issuing_authorization_release, issuing_dispute, issuing_transaction, payment, payment_failure_refund, payment_refund, payout, payout_cancel, payout_failure, refund, refund_failure, reserve_transaction, reserved_funds, stripe_fee, stripe_fx_fee, tax_fee, topup, topup_reversal, transfer, transfer_cancel, transfer_failure, or transfer_refund.

source.stripe.stripe.card.name: card
source.stripe.stripe.card.description: Details of a credit card that has been saved to the system.

account_id.name: account_id
account_id.description: ID of account associated with this card.

address_city.name: address_city
address_city.description: City, district, suburb, town, or village.

address_line_1.name: address_line_1
address_line_1.description: Address line 1 (e.g., street, PO Box, or company name).

address_line_2.name: address_line_2
address_line_2.description: Address line 2 (e.g., apartment, suite, unit, or building).

brand.name: brand
brand.description: Card brand. Can be American Express, Diners Club, Discover, JCB, MasterCard, UnionPay, Visa, or Unknown.

country.name: country
country.description: Two-letter ISO code representing the country of the card. You could use this attribute to get a sense of the international breakdown of cards you’ve collected.

created.name: created
created.description: Time at which the record was created. Dates in the requested timezone, or UTC if not provided.

customer_id.name: customer_id
customer_id.description: The customer that this card belongs to.  NULL if belongs to an account or recipient.

recipient.name: recipient
recipient.description: The recipient that this card belongs to. NULL if the card belongs to a customer or account instead.

funding.name: funding
funding.description: Card funding type. Can be credit, debit, prepaid, or unknown.

wallet_type.name: wallet_type
wallet_type.description: The type of the card wallet, one of amex_express_checkout, apple_pay, google_pay, masterpass, samsung_pay, or visa_checkout. An additional hash is included on the Wallet subhash with a name matching this value. It contains additional information specific to the card wallet type.

three_d_secure_authentication_flow.name: three_d_secure_authentication_flow
three_d_secure_authentication_flow.description: For authenticated transactions, how the customer was authenticated by the issuing bank.

three_d_secure_result.name: three_d_secure_result
three_d_secure_result.description: Indicates the outcome of 3D Secure authentication.

three_d_secure_result_reason.name: three_d_secure_result_reason
three_d_secure_result_reason.description: Additional information about why 3D Secure succeeded or failed based on the result.

three_d_secure_version.name: three_d_secure_version
three_d_secure_version.description: The version of 3D Secure that was used.

source.stripe.stripe.charge.name: charge
source.stripe.stripe.charge.description: To charge a credit or a debit card, you create a Charge object. You can retrieve and refund individual charges as well as list all charges. Charges are identified by a unique, random ID.

amount.name: amount
amount.description: Amount intended to be collected by this payment. A positive integer representing how much to charge in the smallest currency unit (e.g., 100 cents to charge $1.00 or 100 to charge ¥100, a zero-decimal currency)

amount_refunded.name: amount_refunded
amount_refunded.description: The amount of the charge, if any, that has been refunded.

application_fee_amount.name: application_fee_amount
application_fee_amount.description: The amount of the application fee (if any) for the charge.

balance_transaction_id.name: balance_transaction_id
balance_transaction_id.description: ID of the balance transaction that describes the impact of this charge on your account balance (not including refunds or disputes).

captured.name: captured
captured.description: If the charge was created without capturing, this Boolean represents whether it is still uncaptured or has since been captured.

card_id.name: card_id
card_id.description: ID of the card that was charged.

created.name: created
created.description: Time at which the record was created. Dates in the requested timezone, or UTC if not provided.

connected_account_id.name: connected_account_id
connected_account_id.description: ID of account connected for this charge.

customer_id.name: customer_id
customer_id.description: ID of the customer this charge is for if one exists.

description.name: description
description.description: An arbitrary string attached to the object. Often useful for displaying to users.

failure_code.name: failure_code
failure_code.description: Error code explaining reason for charge failure if available.

failure_message.name: failure_message
failure_message.description: Message to user further explaining reason for charge failure if available.

metadata.name: metadata
metadata.description: Custom metadata added to the record, in JSON string format

paid.name: paid
paid.description: true if the charge succeeded, or was successfully authorized for later capture.

payment_intent_id.name: payment_intent_id
payment_intent_id.description: ID of the PaymentIntent associated with this charge, if one exists.

receipt_email.name: receipt_email
receipt_email.description: This is the email address that the receipt for this charge was sent to.

receipt_number.name: receipt_number
receipt_number.description: This is the transaction number that appears on email receipts sent for this charge.

refunded.name: refunded
refunded.description: Whether the charge has been fully refunded. If the charge is only partially refunded, this attribute will still be false.

status.name: status
status.description: The status of the payment is either succeeded, pending, or failed.

shipping_address_city.name: shipping_address_city
shipping_address_city.description: City, district, suburb, town, or village.

shipping_address_line_1.name: shipping_address_line_1
shipping_address_line_1.description: Address line 1 (e.g., street, PO Box, or company name).

shipping_address_line_2.name: shipping_address_line_2
shipping_address_line_2.description: Address line 2 (e.g., apartment, suite, unit, or building).

shipping_carrier.name: shipping_carrier
shipping_carrier.description: The delivery service that shipped a physical product, such as Fedex, UPS, USPS, etc.

shipping_tracking_number.name: shipping_tracking_number
shipping_tracking_number.description: The tracking number for a physical product, obtained from the delivery service. If multiple tracking numbers were generated for this purchase, please separate them with commas.

source_id.name: source_id
source_id.description: ID of the source associated. Source objects allow you to accept a variety of payment methods. They represent a customer's payment instrument, and can be used with the Stripe API just like a Card object, once chargeable, they can be charged, or can be attached to customers.

source_transfer.name: source_transfer
source_transfer.description: The transfer ID which created this charge. Only present if the charge came from another Stripe account.

statement_descriptor.name: statement_descriptor
statement_descriptor.description: Extra information about a source. This will appear on your customer’s statement every time you charge the source.

invoice_id.name: invoice_id
invoice_id.description: The id of the invoice associated with this charge.

currency.name: currency
currency.description: The currency of the charge.

livemode.name: livemode
livemode.description: Indicates if this is a test charge.

payment_method_id.name: payment_method_id
payment_method_id.description: Unique identifier for the payment method object used in this charge.

calculated_statement_descriptor.name: calculated_statement_descriptor
calculated_statement_descriptor.description: The full statement descriptor that is passed to card networks, and that is displayed on your customers’ credit card and bank statements. Allows you to see what the statement descriptor looks like after the static and dynamic portions are combined.

billing_detail_address_city.name: billing_detail_address_city
billing_detail_address_city.description: City, district, suburb, town, or village.

billing_detail_address_line1.name: billing_detail_address_line1
billing_detail_address_line1.description: Address line 1 (e.g., street, PO Box, or company name).

billing_detail_address_line2.name: billing_detail_address_line2
billing_detail_address_line2.description: Address line 2 (e.g., apartment, suite, unit, or building).

source.stripe.stripe.customer.name: customer
source.stripe.stripe.customer.description: Customer objects allow you to perform recurring charges, and to track multiple charges, that are associated with the same customer.

account_balance.name: account_balance
account_balance.description: Current balance, if any, being stored on the customer. If negative, the customer has credit to apply to their next invoice. If positive, the customer has an amount owed that will be added to their next invoice.

address_city.name: address_city
address_city.description: City, district, suburb, town, or village.

address_line_1.name: address_line_1
address_line_1.description: Address line 1 (e.g., street, PO Box, or company name).

address_line_2.name: address_line_2
address_line_2.description: Address line 2 (e.g., apartment, suite, unit, or building).

balance.name: balance
balance.description: Current balance, if any, being stored on the customer. If negative, the customer has credit to apply to their next invoice. If positive, the customer has an amount owed that will be added to their next invoice. The balance does not refer to any unpaid invoices; it solely takes into account amounts that have yet to be successfully applied to any invoice. This balance is only taken into account as invoices are finalized.

bank_account_id.name: bank_account_id
bank_account_id.description: ID of the bank account associated with this customer.

created.name: created
created.description: Time at which the record was created. Dates in the requested timezone, or UTC if not provided.

currency.name: currency
currency.description: Three-letter ISO code for the currency the customer can be charged in for recurring billing purposes.

default_card_id.name: default_card_id
default_card_id.description: ID for the default card used by the customer.

delinquent.name: delinquent
delinquent.description: When the customer’s latest invoice is billed by charging automatically, delinquent is true if the invoice’s latest charge is failed. When the customer’s latest invoice is billed by sending an invoice, delinquent is true if the invoice is not paid by its due date.

description.name: description
description.description: An arbitrary string attached to the object. Often useful for displaying to users.

metadata.name: metadata
metadata.description: Custom metadata added to the record, in JSON string format

shipping_address_city.name: shipping_address_city
shipping_address_city.description: Attribute of the customer's shipping address.

shipping_address_country.name: shipping_address_country
shipping_address_country.description: Attribute of the customer's shipping address.

shipping_address_line_1.name: shipping_address_line_1
shipping_address_line_1.description: Attribute of the customer's shipping address.

shipping_address_line_2.name: shipping_address_line_2
shipping_address_line_2.description: Attribute of the customer's shipping address.

shipping_address_postal_code.name: shipping_address_postal_code
shipping_address_postal_code.description: Attribute of the customer's shipping address.

shipping_address_state.name: shipping_address_state
shipping_address_state.description: Attribute of the customer's shipping address.

shipping_name.name: shipping_name
shipping_name.description: Attribute of the customer's shipping address.

shipping_phone.name: shipping_phone
shipping_phone.description: Attribute of the customer's shipping address.

livemode.name: livemode
livemode.description: Indicates if this is a test customer.

is_deleted.name: is_deleted
is_deleted.description: Boolean reflecting whether the customer has been deleted in Stripe.

source.stripe.stripe.dispute.name: dispute
source.stripe.stripe.dispute.description: The details of a dispute related to a charge. A dispute occurs when a customer questions your charge with their card issuer. When this happens, you're given the opportunity to respond to the dispute with evidence that shows that the charge is legitimate.

amount.name: amount
amount.description: Disputed amount. Usually the amount of the charge, but can differ (usually because of currency fluctuation or because only part of the order is disputed).

balance_transaction.name: balance_transaction
balance_transaction.description: List of zero, one, or two balance transactions that show funds withdrawn and reinstated to your Stripe account as a result of this dispute.

charge_id.name: charge_id
charge_id.description: ID of the charge that was disputed.

connected_account_id.name: connected_account_id
connected_account_id.description: Account id associated with this dispute.

created.name: created
created.description: Time at which the object was created. Measured in seconds since the Unix epoch.

currency.name: currency
currency.description: Three-letter ISO currency code, in lowercase. Must be a supported currency.

evidence_access_activity_log.name: evidence_access_activity_log
evidence_access_activity_log.description: Any server or activity logs showing proof that the customer accessed or downloaded the purchased digital product. This information should include IP addresses, corresponding timestamps, and any detailed recorded activity. Has a maximum character count of 20,000.

evidence_billing_address.name: evidence_billing_address
evidence_billing_address.description: The billing address provided by the customer.

evidence_cancellation_policy.name: evidence_cancellation_policy
evidence_cancellation_policy.description: (ID of a file upload) Your subscription cancellation policy, as shown to the customer.

evidence_cancellation_policy_disclosure.name: evidence_cancellation_policy_disclosure
evidence_cancellation_policy_disclosure.description: An explanation of how and when the customer was shown your refund policy prior to purchase. Has a maximum character count of 20,000.

evidence_cancellation_rebuttal.name: evidence_cancellation_rebuttal
evidence_cancellation_rebuttal.description: A justification for why the customer’s subscription was not canceled. Has a maximum character count of 20,000.

evidence_customer_communication.name: evidence_customer_communication
evidence_customer_communication.description: (ID of a file upload) Any communication with the customer that you feel is relevant to your case. Examples include emails proving that the customer received the product or service, or demonstrating their use of or satisfaction with the product or service.

evidence_customer_email_address.name: evidence_customer_email_address
evidence_customer_email_address.description: The email address of the customer.

evidence_customer_purchase_ip.name: evidence_customer_purchase_ip
evidence_customer_purchase_ip.description: The IP address that the customer used when making the purchase.

evidence_customer_signature.name: evidence_customer_signature
evidence_customer_signature.description: (ID of a file upload) A relevant document or contract showing the customer’s signature.

evidence_details_due_by.name: evidence_details_due_by
evidence_details_due_by.description: Date by which evidence must be submitted in order to successfully challenge dispute. Will be 0 if the customer’s bank or credit card company doesn’t allow a response for this particular dispute.

evidence_details_has_evidence.name: evidence_details_has_evidence
evidence_details_has_evidence.description: Whether evidence has been staged for this dispute.

evidence_details_past_due.name: evidence_details_past_due
evidence_details_past_due.description: Whether the last evidence submission was submitted past the due date. Defaults to false if no evidence submissions have occurred. If true, then delivery of the latest evidence is not guaranteed.

evidence_details_submission_count.name: evidence_details_submission_count
evidence_details_submission_count.description: The number of times evidence has been submitted. Typically, you may only submit evidence once.

evidence_duplicate_charge_documentation.name: evidence_duplicate_charge_documentation
evidence_duplicate_charge_documentation.description: (ID of a file upload) Documentation for the prior charge that can uniquely identify the charge, such as a receipt, shipping label, work order, etc. This document should be paired with a similar document from the disputed payment that proves the two payments are separate.

evidence_duplicate_charge_explanation.name: evidence_duplicate_charge_explanation
evidence_duplicate_charge_explanation.description: An explanation of the difference between the disputed charge versus the prior charge that appears to be a duplicate. Has a maximum character count of 20,000.

evidence_duplicate_charge_id.name: evidence_duplicate_charge_id
evidence_duplicate_charge_id.description: The Stripe ID for the prior charge which appears to be a duplicate of the disputed charge.

evidence_product_description.name: evidence_product_description
evidence_product_description.description: A description of the product or service that was sold. Has a maximum character count of 20,000.

evidence_receipt.name: evidence_receipt
evidence_receipt.description: (ID of a file upload) Any receipt or message sent to the customer notifying them of the charge.

evidence_refund_policy.name: evidence_refund_policy
evidence_refund_policy.description: (ID of a file upload) Your refund policy, as shown to the customer.

evidence_refund_policy_disclosure.name: evidence_refund_policy_disclosure
evidence_refund_policy_disclosure.description: Documentation demonstrating that the customer was shown your refund policy prior to purchase. Has a maximum character count of 20,000.

evidence_refund_refusal_explanation.name: evidence_refund_refusal_explanation
evidence_refund_refusal_explanation.description: A justification for why the customer is not entitled to a refund. Has a maximum character count of 20,000.

evidence_service_date.name: evidence_service_date
evidence_service_date.description: The date on which the customer received or began receiving the purchased service, in a clear human-readable format.

evidence_service_documentation.name: evidence_service_documentation
evidence_service_documentation.description: (ID of a file upload) Documentation showing proof that a service was provided to the customer. This could include a copy of a signed contract, work order, or other form of written agreement.

evidence_shipping_address.name: evidence_shipping_address
evidence_shipping_address.description: The address to which a physical product was shipped. You should try to include as complete address information as possible.

evidence_shipping_carrier.name: evidence_shipping_carrier
evidence_shipping_carrier.description: The delivery service that shipped a physical product, such as Fedex, UPS, USPS, etc. If multiple carriers were used for this purchase, please separate them with commas.

evidence_shipping_date.name: evidence_shipping_date
evidence_shipping_date.description: The date on which a physical product began its route to the shipping address, in a clear human-readable format.

evidence_shipping_documentation.name: evidence_shipping_documentation
evidence_shipping_documentation.description: (ID of a file upload) Documentation showing proof that a product was shipped to the customer at the same address the customer provided to you. This could include a copy of the shipment receipt, shipping label, etc. It should show the customer’s full shipping address, if possible.

evidence_shipping_tracking_number.name: evidence_shipping_tracking_number
evidence_shipping_tracking_number.description: The tracking number for a physical product, obtained from the delivery service. If multiple tracking numbers were generated for this purchase, please separate them with commas.

evidence_uncategorized_file.name: evidence_uncategorized_file
evidence_uncategorized_file.description: (ID of a file upload) Any additional evidence or statements.

evidence_uncategorized_text.name: evidence_uncategorized_text
evidence_uncategorized_text.description: Any additional evidence or statements. Has a maximum character count of 20,000.

is_charge_refundable.name: is_charge_refundable
is_charge_refundable.description: Boolean ff true, it is still possible to refund the disputed payment. Once the payment has been fully refunded, no further funds will be withdrawn from your Stripe account as a result of this dispute.

livemode.name: livemode
livemode.description: Indicates if this is a test dispute.

metadata.name: metadata
metadata.description: Custom metadata added to the record, in JSON string format

reason.name: reason
reason.description: Reason given by cardholder for dispute. Possible values are bank_cannot_process, check_returned, credit_not_processed, customer_initiated, debit_not_authorized, duplicate, fraudulent, general, incorrect_account_details, insufficient_funds, product_not_received, product_unacceptable, subscription_canceled, or unrecognized.

status.name: status
status.description: Current status of dispute. Possible values are warning_needs_response, warning_under_review, warning_closed, needs_response, under_review, won, or lost.

source.stripe.stripe.fee.name: fee
source.stripe.stripe.fee.description: The details of a fee associated with a balance_transaction

balance_transaction_id.name: balance_transaction_id
balance_transaction_id.description: ID of the balance transaction entry the fee applies to

index.name: index
index.description: The index of the fee within the balance transaction

amount.name: amount
amount.description: Amount of the fee, in cents.

application.name: application
application.description: ID of the Connect application that earned the fee.

currency.name: currency
currency.description: Three-letter ISO currency code, in lowercase.

description.name: description
description.description: An arbitrary string attached to the object. Often useful for displaying to users.

type.name: type
type.description: Type of the fee, can be application_fee, stripe_fee or tax.

source.stripe.stripe.payment_intent.name: payment_intent
source.stripe.stripe.payment_intent.description: A Payment Intent guides you through the process of collecting a payment from your customer.

amount.name: amount
amount.description: Amount intended to be collected by this PaymentIntent. A positive integer representing how much to charge in the smallest currency unit (e.g., 100 cents to charge $1.00 or 100 to charge ¥100, a zero-decimal currency)

amount_capturable.name: amount_capturable
amount_capturable.description: Amount that can be captured from this PaymentIntent.

amount_received.name: amount_received
amount_received.description: Amount that was collected by this PaymentIntent.

application.name: application
application.description: ID of the Connect application that created the PaymentIntent.

application_fee_amount.name: application_fee_amount
application_fee_amount.description: The amount of the application fee (if any) for the resulting payment.

canceled_at.name: canceled_at
canceled_at.description: Populated when status is canceled, this is the time at which the PaymentIntent was canceled.

cancellation_reason.name: cancellation_reason
cancellation_reason.description: Reason for cancellation of this PaymentIntent, either user-provided (duplicate, fraudulent, requested_by_customer, or abandoned) or generated by Stripe internally (failed_invoice, void_invoice, or automatic).

capture_method.name: capture_method
capture_method.description: Controls when the funds will be captured from the customer’s account.

currency.name: currency
currency.description: Three-letter ISO currency code, in lowercase.

customer_id.name: customer_id
customer_id.description: ID of the Customer this PaymentIntent belongs to, if one exists.

description.name: description
description.description: An arbitrary string attached to the object. Often useful for displaying to users.

metadata.name: metadata
metadata.description: Custom metadata added to the record, in JSON string format

payment_method_id.name: payment_method_id
payment_method_id.description: ID of the payment method used in this PaymentIntent.

receipt_email.name: receipt_email
receipt_email.description: Email address that the receipt for the resulting payment will be sent to.

statement_descriptor.name: statement_descriptor
statement_descriptor.description: For non-card charges, you can use this value as the complete description that appears on your customers’ statements.

status.name: status
status.description: Status of this PaymentIntent, one of requires_payment_method, requires_confirmation, requires_action, processing, requires_capture, canceled, or succeeded.

livemode.name: livemode
livemode.description: Indicates if this is a test payment intent.

source.stripe.stripe.payment_method_card.name: payment_method_card
source.stripe.stripe.payment_method_card.description: Table with the relationships between a payment method and a card

brand.name: brand
brand.description: Card brand. Can be American Express, Diners Club, Discover, JCB, MasterCard, UnionPay, Visa, or Unknown.

funding.name: funding
funding.description: Card funding type. Can be credit, debit, prepaid, or unknown.

charge_id.name: charge_id
charge_id.description: ID of the charge that this card belongs to.

type.name: type
type.description: The type of the payment method.

wallet_type.name: wallet_type
wallet_type.description: The type of the card wallet, one of amex_express_checkout, apple_pay, google_pay, masterpass, samsung_pay, or visa_checkout. An additional hash is included on the Wallet subhash with a name matching this value. It contains additional information specific to the card wallet type.

source.stripe.stripe.payment_method.name: payment_method
source.stripe.stripe.payment_method.description: PaymentMethod objects represent your customer's payment instruments. They can be used with PaymentIntents to collect payments or saved to Customer objects to store instrument details for future payments.

created.name: created
created.description: Time at which the record was created. Dates in the requested timezone, or UTC if not provided.

customer_id.name: customer_id
customer_id.description: The ID of the Customer to which this PaymentMethod is saved. This will not be set when the PaymentMethod has not been saved to a Customer.

metadata.name: metadata
metadata.description: Custom metadata added to the record, in JSON string format

type.name: type
type.description: The type of the PaymentMethod. An additional hash is included on the PaymentMethod with a name matching this value. It contains additional information specific to the PaymentMethod type.

livemode.name: livemode
livemode.description: Indicates if this is a test payment method.

source.stripe.stripe.payout.name: payout
source.stripe.stripe.payout.description: A Payout object is created when you receive funds from Stripe, or when you initiate a payout to either a bank account or debit card of a connected Stripe account.

amount.name: amount
amount.description: Amount (in cents) to be transferred to your bank account or debit card.

arrival_date.name: arrival_date
arrival_date.description: Date the payout is expected to arrive in the bank. This factors in delays like weekends or bank holidays.

automatic.name: automatic
automatic.description: true if the payout was created by an automated payout schedule, and false if it was requested manually.

balance_transaction_id.name: balance_transaction_id
balance_transaction_id.description: ID of the balance transaction that describes the impact of this payout on your account balance.

created.name: created
created.description: Time at which the record was created. Dates in the requested timezone, or UTC if not provided.

currency.name: currency
currency.description: Three-letter ISO currency code, in lowercase.

description.name: description
description.description: An arbitrary string attached to the object. Often useful for displaying to users.

destination_bank_account_id.name: destination_bank_account_id
destination_bank_account_id.description: ID of the bank account the payout was sent to.

destination_card_id.name: destination_card_id
destination_card_id.description: ID of the card the payout was sent to.

metadata.name: metadata
metadata.description: Custom metadata added to the record, in JSON string format

method.name: method
method.description: The method used to send this payout, which can be standard or instant.

source_type.name: source_type
source_type.description: The source balance this payout came from. One of card, fpx, or bank_account.

status.name: status
status.description: Current status of the payout.  Can be paid, pending, in_transit, canceled or failed.

type.name: type
type.description: Can be bank_account or card.

livemode.name: livemode
livemode.description: Indicates if this is a test payout.

source.stripe.stripe.payout_balance_tran.name: payout_balance_transaction
source.stripe.stripe.payout_balance_tran.description: Table that contains the complete mapping between `payout_id` and `balance_transaction_id`. The payout to balance_transaction relationship is 1:many.

balance_transaction_id.name: balance_transaction_id
balance_transaction_id.description: Unique identifier for the balance transaction.

_fivetran_synced.name: _fivetran_synced
_fivetran_synced.description: Timestamp when the record was last synced.

source.stripe.stripe.refund.name: refund
source.stripe.stripe.refund.description: Details of transactions that have been refunded

amount.name: amount
amount.description: Amount, in cents.

balance_transaction_id.name: balance_transaction_id
balance_transaction_id.description: ID of the latest balance transaction linked to this payout, describing its impact on your account balance. The payout to balance_transaction relationship is 1:many.

charge_id.name: charge_id
charge_id.description: ID of the charge that was refunded.

created.name: created
created.description: Time at which the record was created. Dates in the requested timezone, or UTC if not provided.

currency.name: currency
currency.description: Three-letter ISO currency code, in lowercase.

description.name: description
description.description: An arbitrary string attached to the object. Often useful for displaying to users. (Available on non-card refunds only)

metadata.name: metadata
metadata.description: Custom metadata added to the record, in JSON string format

payment_intent_id.name: payment_intent_id
payment_intent_id.description: ID of the payment intent associated with this refund.

reason.name: reason
reason.description: Reason for the refund, either user-provided (duplicate, fraudulent, or requested_by_customer) or generated by Stripe internally (expired_uncaptured_charge).

receipt_number.name: receipt_number
receipt_number.description: This is the transaction number that appears on email receipts sent for this refund.

status.name: status
status.description: Status of the refund. For credit card refunds, this can be pending, succeeded, or failed. For other types of refunds, it can be pending, succeeded, failed, or canceled.

source.stripe.stripe.invoice_line_item.name: invoice_line_item
source.stripe.stripe.invoice_line_item.description: The different items that an invoice contains

invoice_id.name: invoice_id
invoice_id.description: The ID of the invoice this item is a part of

invoice_item_id.name: invoice_item_id
invoice_item_id.description: The ID of the invoice item this item is a part of

price_id.name: price_id
price_id.description: ID of the price object this item pertains to

amount.name: amount
amount.description: The amount, in cents.

currency.name: currency
currency.description: Three-letter ISO currency code, in lowercase.

description.name: description
description.description: An arbitrary string attached to the object. Often useful for displaying to users.

discountable.name: discountable
discountable.description: If true, discounts will apply to this line item. Always false for prorations.

plan_id.name: plan_id
plan_id.description: The ID of the plan of the subscription, if the line item is a subscription or a proration.

quantity.name: quantity
quantity.description: The quantity of the subscription, if the line item is a subscription or a proration.

subscription_id.name: subscription_id
subscription_id.description: The ID of the subscription that the invoice item pertains to, if any.

subscription_item_id.name: subscription_item_id
subscription_item_id.description: The subscription item that generated this invoice item. Left empty if the line item is not an explicit result of a subscription.

type.name: type
type.description: A string identifying the type of the source of this line item, either an invoice item or a subscription.

unique_id.name: unique_id
unique_id.description: A unique id generated and only for old invoice line item ID's from a past version of the API. The introduction of this field resolves the pagination break issue for invoice line items, which was introduced by the [Stripe API update](https://stripe.com/docs/upgrades#2019-12-03).

livemode.name: livemode
livemode.description: Indicates if this is a test invoice line item.

source.stripe.stripe.invoice.name: invoice
source.stripe.stripe.invoice.description: Invoices are statements of amounts owed by a customer, and are either generated one-off, or generated periodically from a subscription.

amount_due.name: amount_due
amount_due.description: Final amount due at this time for this invoice. If the invoice’s total is smaller than the minimum charge amount, for example, or if there is account credit that can be applied to the invoice, the amount_due may be 0. If there is a positive starting_balance for the invoice (the customer owes money), the amount_due will also take that into account. The charge that gets generated for the invoice will be for the amount specified in amount_due.

amount_paid.name: amount_paid
amount_paid.description: The amount, in cents, that was paid.

amount_remaining.name: amount_remaining
amount_remaining.description: The amount remaining, in cents, that is due.

attempt_count.name: attempt_count
attempt_count.description: Number of payment attempts made for this invoice, from the perspective of the payment retry schedule.

auto_advance.name: auto_advance
auto_advance.description: Controls whether Stripe will perform automatic collection of the invoice. When false, the invoice’s state will not automatically advance without an explicit action.

billing_reason.name: billing_reason
billing_reason.description: Indicates the reason why the invoice was created.

charge_id.name: charge_id
charge_id.description: ID of the latest charge generated for this invoice, if any.

created.name: created
created.description: Time at which the record was created. Dates in the requested timezone, or UTC if not provided.

currency.name: currency
currency.description: Three-letter ISO currency code, in lowercase.

customer_id.name: customer_id
customer_id.description: The ID of the customer who will be billed.

description.name: description
description.description: An arbitrary string attached to the object. Often useful for displaying to users. Referenced as ‘memo’ in the Dashboard.

due_date.name: due_date
due_date.description: The date on which payment for this invoice is due. This value will be null for invoices where collection_method=charge_automatically.

metadata.name: metadata
metadata.description: Custom metadata added to the record, in JSON string format

number.name: number
number.description: A unique, identifying string that appears on emails sent to the customer for this invoice. This starts with the customer’s unique invoice_prefix if it is specified.

paid.name: paid
paid.description: Whether payment was successfully collected for this invoice. An invoice can be paid (most commonly) with a charge or with credit from the customer’s account balance.

receipt_number.name: receipt_number
receipt_number.description: This is the transaction number that appears on email receipts sent for this invoice.

subscription_id.name: subscription_id
subscription_id.description: The ID of the subscription that the invoice pertains to,.

subtotal.name: subtotal
subtotal.description: Total of all subscriptions, invoice items, and prorations on the invoice before any discount or tax is applied.

tax.name: tax
tax.description: The amount of tax on this invoice. This is the sum of all the tax amounts on this invoice.

tax_percent.name: tax_percent
tax_percent.description: The percent used to calculate the tax amount.

livemode.name: livemode
livemode.description: Indicates if this is a test invoice.

period_start.name: period_start
period_start.description: Start of the usage period during for which the invoice was created.

period_end.name: period_end
period_end.description: End of the usage period during for which the invoice was created.

default_payment_method_id.name: default_payment_method_id
default_payment_method_id.description: ID of the default payment method in this invoice.

payment_intent_id.name: payment_intent_id
payment_intent_id.description: ID of the PaymentIntent associated with this invoice.

post_payment_credit_notes_amount.name: post_payment_credit_notes_amount
post_payment_credit_notes_amount.description: Total amount of all post-payment credit notes issued for this invoice.

pre_payment_credit_notes_amount.name: pre_payment_credit_notes_amount
pre_payment_credit_notes_amount.description: Total amount of all pre-payment credit notes issued for this invoice.

status_transitions_finalized_at.name: status_transitions_finalized_at
status_transitions_finalized_at.description: The time that the invoice draft was finalized.

status_transitions_marked_uncollectible_.name: status_transitions_marked_uncollectible_at
status_transitions_marked_uncollectible_.description: The time that the invoice was marked uncollectible.

status_transitions_paid_at.name: status_transitions_paid_at
status_transitions_paid_at.description: The time that the invoice was paid.

status_transitions_voided_at.name: status_transitions_voided_at
status_transitions_voided_at.description: The time that the invoice was voided.

source.stripe.stripe.subscription_histor.name: subscription_history
source.stripe.stripe.subscription_histor.description: Subscriptions allow you to charge a customer on a recurring basis. Please note this source table is used only on connectors setup **after** February 09, 2022.

status.name: status
status.description: Possible values are incomplete, incomplete_expired, trialing, active, past_due, canceled, or unpaid.

billing_cycle_anchor.name: billing_cycle_anchor
billing_cycle_anchor.description: Determines the date of the first full invoice, and, for plans with month or year intervals, the day of the month for subsequent invoices.

cancel_at.name: cancel_at
cancel_at.description: A date in the future at which the subscription will automatically get canceled

cancel_at_period_end.name: cancel_at_period_end
cancel_at_period_end.description: Boolean indicating whether this subscription should cancel at the end of the current period.

canceled_at.name: canceled_at
canceled_at.description: If the subscription has been canceled, the date of that cancellation.

created.name: created
created.description: Time at which the record was created. Dates in the requested timezone, or UTC if not provided.

current_period_start.name: current_period_start
current_period_start.description: Start of the current period that the subscription has been invoiced for.

current_period_end.name: current_period_end
current_period_end.description: End of the current period that the subscription has been invoiced for. At the end of this period, a new invoice will be created.

customer_id.name: customer_id
customer_id.description: ID of customer this subscription belongs to.

days_until_due.name: days_until_due
days_until_due.description: Number of days a customer has to pay invoices generated by this subscription. This value will be null for subscriptions where collection_method=charge_automatically.

metadata.name: metadata
metadata.description: Custom metadata added to the record, in JSON string format

start_date.name: start_date
start_date.description: Date when the subscription was first created. The date might differ from the created date due to backdating.

ended_at.name: ended_at
ended_at.description: If the subscription has ended, the date the subscription ended.

livemode.name: livemode
livemode.description: Indicates if this is a test subscription.

_fivetran_active.name: _fivetran_active
_fivetran_active.description: Boolean indicating if the record is the latest.

latest_invoice_id.name: latest_invoice_id
latest_invoice_id.description: ID of the latest invoice for this subscription.

default_payment_method_id.name: default_payment_method_id
default_payment_method_id.description: ID of the default payment method for this subscription.

pending_setup_intent_id.name: pending_setup_intent_id
pending_setup_intent_id.description: ID of the payment setup intent for this subscription.

pause_collection_behavior.name: pause_collection_behavior
pause_collection_behavior.description: The payment collection behavior for this subscription while paused. One of keep_as_draft, mark_uncollectible, or void.

pause_collection_resumes_at.name: pause_collection_resumes_at
pause_collection_resumes_at.description: The time after which the subscription will resume collecting payments.

source.stripe.stripe.subscription.name: subscription
source.stripe.stripe.subscription.description: Subscriptions allow you to charge a customer on a recurring basis. Please note this source table is only present in connectors setup **before** February 09, 2022.

status.name: status
status.description: Possible values are incomplete, incomplete_expired, trialing, active, past_due, canceled, or unpaid.

billing_cycle_anchor.name: billing_cycle_anchor
billing_cycle_anchor.description: Determines the date of the first full invoice, and, for plans with month or year intervals, the day of the month for subsequent invoices.

cancel_at.name: cancel_at
cancel_at.description: A date in the future at which the subscription will automatically get canceled

cancel_at_period_end.name: cancel_at_period_end
cancel_at_period_end.description: Boolean indicating whether this subscription should cancel at the end of the current period.

canceled_at.name: canceled_at
canceled_at.description: If the subscription has been canceled, the date of that cancellation.

created.name: created
created.description: Time at which the record was created. Dates in the requested timezone, or UTC if not provided.

current_period_start.name: current_period_start
current_period_start.description: Start of the current period that the subscription has been invoiced for.

current_period_end.name: current_period_end
current_period_end.description: End of the current period that the subscription has been invoiced for. At the end of this period, a new invoice will be created.

customer_id.name: customer_id
customer_id.description: ID of the customer who owns the subscription.

days_until_due.name: days_until_due
days_until_due.description: Number of days a customer has to pay invoices generated by this subscription. This value will be null for subscriptions where collection_method=charge_automatically.

metadata.name: metadata

start_date.name: start_date
start_date.description: Date when the subscription was first created. The date might differ from the created date due to backdating.

ended_at.name: ended_at
ended_at.description: If the subscription has ended, the date the subscription ended.

livemode.name: livemode
livemode.description: Indicates if this is a test subscription.

pause_collection_behavior.name: pause_collection_behavior
pause_collection_behavior.description: The payment collection behavior for this subscription while paused. One of keep_as_draft, mark_uncollectible, or void.

pause_collection_resumes_at.name: pause_collection_resumes_at
pause_collection_resumes_at.description: The time after which the subscription will resume collecting payments.

source.stripe.stripe.plan.name: plan
source.stripe.stripe.plan.description: Plans define the base price, currency, and billing cycle for recurring purchases of products.

active.name: active
active.description: Whether the plan can be used for new purchases.

amount.name: amount
amount.description: The unit amount in cents to be charged, represented as a whole integer if possible.

currency.name: currency
currency.description: Three-letter ISO currency code, in lowercase.

interval.name: interval
interval.description: The frequency at which a subscription is billed. One of day, week, month or year.

interval_count.name: interval_count
interval_count.description: The number of intervals between subscription billings. For example, interval_count=3 bills every 3 months.

metadata.name: metadata
metadata.description: Custom metadata added to the record, in JSON string format

nickname.name: nickname
nickname.description: A brief description of the plan, hidden from customers.

product.name: product
product.description: The product whose pricing this plan determines.

livemode.name: livemode
livemode.description: Indicates if this is a test plan.

source.stripe.stripe.credit_note.name: credit_note
source.stripe.stripe.credit_note.description: Credit notes are documents that decrease the amount owed on an invoice. They’re the only way to adjust the amount of a finalized invoice other than voiding and recreating the invoice.

amount.name: amount
amount.description: The integer amount in cents representing the total amount of the credit note, including tax.

created.name: created
created.description: Time at which the record was created. Dates in the requested timezone, or UTC if not provided.

currency.name: currency
currency.description: The currency of the charge. Three-letter ISO currency code, in lowercase.

discount_amount.name: discount_amount
discount_amount.description: The integer amount in cents representing the total amount of discount that was credited.

subtotal.name: subtotal
subtotal.description: The integer amount in cents representing the amount of the credit note, excluding tax and invoice level discounts.

total.name: total
total.description: The integer amount in cents representing the total amount of the credit note, including tax and all discount.

livemode.name: livemode
livemode.description: Has the value true if the object exists in live mode or the value false if the object exists in test mode.

memo.name: memo
memo.description: Customer-facing text that appears on the credit note PDF.

metadata.name: metadata
metadata.description: Set of key-value pairs that you can attach to an object. This can be useful for storing additional information about the object in a structured format.

number.name: number
number.description: A unique number that identifies this particular credit note and appears on the PDF of the credit note and its associated invoice.

pdf.name: pdf
pdf.description: The link to download the PDF of the credit note.

reason.name: reason
reason.description: Reason for issuing this credit note, one of duplicate, fraudulent, order_change, or product_unsatisfactory

status.name: status
status.description: Status of this credit note, one of issued or void. Learn more about voiding credit notes.

type.name: type
type.description: Type of this credit note, one of pre_payment or post_payment. A pre_payment credit note means it was issued when the invoice was open. A post_payment credit note means it was issued when the invoice was paid.

voided_at.name: voided_at
voided_at.description: The time that the credit note was voided.

customer_balance_transaction.name: customer_balance_transaction
customer_balance_transaction.description: Customer balance transaction related to this credit note.

invoice_id.name: invoice_id
invoice_id.description: The id of the invoice associated with this credit note.

refund_id.name: refund_id
refund_id.description: The id of the refund associated with this credit note.

source.stripe.stripe.credit_note_line_it.name: credit_note_line_item
source.stripe.stripe.credit_note_line_it.description: The different items that a credit note contains.

credit_note_id.name: credit_note_id
credit_note_id.description: The ID of the credit note this item is a part of.

amount.name: amount
amount.description: The integer amount in cents representing the gross amount being credited for this line item, excluding (exclusive) tax and discounts.

discount_amount.name: discount_amount
discount_amount.description: The integer amount in cents representing the discount being credited for this line item.

description.name: description
description.description: Description of the item being credited.

livemode.name: livemode
livemode.description: Has the value true if the object exists in live mode or the value false if the object exists in test mode.

quantity.name: quantity
quantity.description: The number of units of product being credited.

type.name: type
type.description: The type of the credit note line item, one of invoice_line_item or custom_line_item. When the type is invoice_line_item there is an additional invoice_line_item property on the resource the value of which is the id of the credited line item on the invoice.

unit_amount.name: unit_amount
unit_amount.description: The cost of each unit of product being credited.

unit_amount_decimal.name: unit_amount_decimal
unit_amount_decimal.description: Same as unit_amount, but contains a decimal value with at most 12 decimal places.

source.stripe.stripe.price.name: price
source.stripe.stripe.price.description: Prices define the unit cost, currency, and (optional) billing cycle for both recurring and one-time purchases of products.

active.name: active
active.description: Whether the price can be used for new purchases.

billing_scheme.name: billing_scheme
billing_scheme.description: Describes how to compute the price per period. Either per_unit or tiered. per_unit indicates that the fixed amount (specified in unit_amount or unit_amount_decimal) will be charged per unit in quantity (for prices with usage_type=licensed), or per unit of total usage (for prices with usage_type=metered). tiered indicates that the unit pricing will be computed using a tiering strategy as defined using the tiers and tiers_mode attributes.

created.name: created
created.description: Time at which the record was created. Dates in the requested timezone, or UTC if not provided.

currency.name: currency
currency.description: Three-letter ISO currency code, in lowercase. Must be a supported currency.

invoice_item_id.name: invoice_item_id
invoice_item_id.description: The ID of the invoice item this record is a part of.

livemode.name: livemode
livemode.description: Has the value true if the object exists in live mode or the value false if the object exists in test mode.

lookup_key.name: lookup_key
lookup_key.description: A lookup key used to retrieve prices dynamically from a static string. This may be up to 200 characters.

metadata.name: metadata
metadata.description: Set of key-value pairs that you can attach to an object. This can be useful for storing additional information about the object in a structured format.

nickname.name: nickname
nickname.description: A brief description of the price, hidden from customers.

product_id.name: product_id
product_id.description: The ID of the product this price is associated with.

recurring_aggregate_usage.name: recurring_aggregate_usage
recurring_aggregate_usage.description: Specifies a usage aggregation strategy for prices of usage_type=metered. Allowed values are sum for summing up all usage during a period, last_during_period for using the last usage record reported within a period, last_ever for using the last usage record ever (across period bounds) or max which uses the usage record with the maximum reported usage during a period. Defaults to sum.

recurring_interval.name: recurring_interval
recurring_interval.description: Specifies billing frequency. Either day, week, month or year.

recurring_interval_count.name: recurring_interval_count
recurring_interval_count.description: The number of intervals between subscription billings. For example, interval=month and interval_count=3 bills every 3 months. Maximum of one year interval allowed (1 year, 12 months, or 52 weeks).

recurring_usage_type.name: recurring_usage_type
recurring_usage_type.description: Configures how the quantity per period should be determined. Can be either metered or licensed. licensed automatically bills the quantity set when adding it to a subscription. metered aggregates the total usage based on usage records. Defaults to licensed.

tiers_mode.name: tiers_mode
tiers_mode.description: Defines if the tiering price should be graduated or volume based. In volume-based tiering, the maximum quantity within a period determines the per unit price. In graduated tiering, pricing can change as the quantity grows.

transform_quantity_divide_by.name: transform_quantity_divide_by
transform_quantity_divide_by.description: Divide usage by this number. Transform Quantity applies a transformation to the reported usage or set quantity before computing the amount billed. Cannot be combined with tiers.

transform_quantity_round.name: transform_quantity_round
transform_quantity_round.description: After division, either round the result up or down. Transform Quantity applies a transformation to the reported usage or set quantity before computing the amount billed. Cannot be combined with tiers.

type.name: type
type.description: One of one_time or recurring depending on whether the price is for a one-time purchase or a recurring (subscription) purchase.

unit_amount.name: unit_amount
unit_amount.description: The unit amount in cents to be charged, represented as a whole integer if possible. Only set if billing_scheme=per_unit.

unit_amount_decimal.name: unit_amount_decimal
unit_amount_decimal.description: The unit amount in cents to be charged, represented as a decimal string with at most 12 decimal places. Only set if billing_scheme=per_unit.

source.stripe.stripe.account.name: account
source.stripe.stripe.account.description: Prices define the unit cost, currency, and (optional) billing cycle for both recurring and one-time purchases of products.

business_profile_mcc.name: business_profile_mcc
business_profile_mcc.description: The merchant category code for the account. MCCs are used to classify businesses based on the goods or services they provide.

charges_enabled.name: charges_enabled
charges_enabled.description: Whether the account can create live charges.

company_address_city.name: company_address_city
company_address_city.description: City, district, suburb, town, or village.

company_address_line_1.name: company_address_line_1
company_address_line_1.description: Address line 1 (e.g., street, PO Box, or company name).

company_address_line_2.name: company_address_line_2
company_address_line_2.description: Address line 2 (e.g., apartment, suite, unit, or building).

company_phone.name: company_phone
company_phone.description: The company’s phone number (used for verification).

created.name: created
created.description: Time at which the record was created. Dates in the requested timezone, or UTC if not provided.

default_currency.name: default_currency
default_currency.description: Three-letter ISO currency code representing the default currency for the account. This must be a currency that Stripe supports in the account’s country.

email.name: email
email.description: An email address associated with the account. You can treat this as metadata; it is not used for authentication or messaging account holders.

is_deleted.name: is_deleted
is_deleted.description: Boolean of whether account has been deleted. Accounts created using test-mode keys can be deleted at any time. Standard accounts created using live-mode keys cannot be deleted. Custom or Express accounts created using live-mode keys can only be deleted once all balances are zero.

metadata.name: metadata
metadata.description: Set of key-value pairs that you can attach to an object. This can be useful for storing additional information about the object in a structured format. Individual keys can be unset by posting an empty value to them. All keys can be unset by posting an empty value to metadata.

payouts_enabled.name: payouts_enabled
payouts_enabled.description: Boolean of whether payouts are enabled.

type.name: type
type.description: Account type

source.stripe.stripe.transfer.name: transfer
source.stripe.stripe.transfer.description: A Transfer object is created when you move funds between Stripe accounts as part of Connect. Before April 6, 2017, transfers also represented movement of funds from a Stripe account to a card or bank account. That has since been moved to the Payout object. The Payout object represents money moving from a Stripe account to an external account (bank or debit card). The Transfer object now only represents money moving between Stripe accounts on a Connect platform.

amount.name: amount
amount.description: Amount in cents to be transferred.

amount_reversed.name: amount_reversed
amount_reversed.description: Amount in cents reversed (can be less than the amount attribute on the transfer if a partial reversal was issued).

balance_transaction_id.name: balance_transaction_id
balance_transaction_id.description: Balance transaction that describes the impact of this transfer on your account balance.

created.name: created
created.description: Time that this record of the transfer was first created.

currency.name: currency
currency.description: Three-letter ISO currency code, in lowercase. Must be a supported currency.

description.name: description
description.description: An arbitrary string attached to the object. Often useful for displaying to users.

destination.name: destination
destination.description: ID of the Stripe account the transfer was sent to.

destination_payment.name: destination_payment
destination_payment.description: If the destination is a Stripe account, the payment that the destination account received for the transfer.

destination_payment_id.name: destination_payment_id
destination_payment_id.description: If the destination is a Stripe account, this will be the ID of the payment that the destination account received for the transfer.

livemode.name: livemode
livemode.description: Indicates if this is a test transfer.

metadata.name: metadata
metadata.description: Custom metadata added to the record, in JSON string format

reversed.name: reversed
reversed.description: Boolean of whether the transfer has been fully reversed. If the transfer is only partially reversed, this attribute will still be false.

source_transaction.name: source_transaction
source_transaction.description: The source transaction related to this transfer.

source_transaction_id.name: source_transaction_id
source_transaction_id.description: ID of the charge or payment that was used to fund the transfer. If null, the transfer was funded from the available balance.

source_type.name: source_type
source_type.description: The source balance this transfer came from. One of card, fpx, or bank_account.

transfer_group.name: transfer_group
transfer_group.description: A string that identifies this transaction as part of a group. See the Connect documentation for details.

source.stripe.stripe.product.name: product
source.stripe.stripe.product.description: A product object represents an individual product to be sold, with various attributes detailing its properties and behaviors.

active.name: active
active.description: Whether the product is currently available for purchase.

attributes.name: attributes
attributes.description: Key-value pairs that can be attached to a product object, useful for storing additional structured information.

caption.name: caption
caption.description: A brief explanation or description of the product for display purposes.

create.name: create
create.description: Timestamp indicating when the product was created.

deactivate_on.name: deactivate_on
deactivate_on.description: List of dates when the product will be deactivated.

description.name: description
description.description: The product’s description, meant to be displayable to the customer.

images.name: images
images.description: A list of up to 8 URLs of images for this product, meant to be displayable to the customer.

is_deleted.name: is_deleted
is_deleted.description: Indicates whether the product has been deleted.

livemode.name: livemode
livemode.description: Indicates if this is a test product.

name.name: name
name.description: The product’s name, meant to be displayable to the customer.

shippable.name: shippable
shippable.description: Whether this product is shipped (i.e., physical goods).

statement_descriptor.name: statement_descriptor
statement_descriptor.description: Extra information about a product which will appear on your customer’s credit card statement.

type.name: type
type.description: The type of the product (e.g., good, service).

unit_label.name: unit_label
unit_label.description: A label that represents units of this product, included in receipts and invoices.

updated.name: updated
updated.description: Time at which the object was last updated, measured in seconds since the Unix epoch.

url.name: url
url.description: A URL of a publicly-accessible webpage for this product.

source.stripe.stripe.discount.name: discount
source.stripe.stripe.discount.description: A discount represents the actual application of a coupon or promotion code. It contains information about when the discount began, when it will end, and what it is applied to.

id.name: id
id.description: The ID of the discount object.

type.name: type
type.description: String representing the object’s type.

type_id.name: type_id
type_id.description: Identifier of the related object type (e.g., coupon ID, promotion code).

amount.name: amount
amount.description: The amount of discount applied.

checkout_session_id.name: checkout_session_id
checkout_session_id.description: The Checkout session that this discount is applied to, if it is applied to a particular session in payment mode.

checkout_session_line_item_id.name: checkout_session_line_item_id
checkout_session_line_item_id.description: The ID of the specific line item within the checkout session that the discount is applied to.

coupon_id.name: coupon_id
coupon_id.description: The ID of the coupon applied to create this discount.

credit_note_line_item_id.name: credit_note_line_item_id
credit_note_line_item_id.description: The ID of the credit note line item associated with this discount.

customer_id.name: customer_id
customer_id.description: The ID of the customer associated with this discount.

end.name: end
end.description: If the coupon has a duration of repeating, the date that this discount will end. If the coupon has a duration of once or forever, this attribute will be null.

invoice_id.name: invoice_id
invoice_id.description: The invoice that the discount’s coupon was applied to, if it was applied directly to a particular invoice.

invoice_item_id.name: invoice_item_id
invoice_item_id.description: The invoice item id (or invoice line item id for invoice line items of type=‘subscription’) that the discount’s coupon was applied to, if it was applied directly to a particular invoice item or invoice line item.

promotion_code.name: promotion_code
promotion_code.description: The promotion code applied to create this discount.

start.name: start
start.description: The date that the coupon was applied.

subscription_id.name: subscription_id
subscription_id.description: The subscription that this coupon is applied to, if it is applied to a particular subscription.

macro.dbt_postgres.postgres__get_relatio.name: postgres__get_relations
macro.dbt_postgres.postgres__get_relatio.macro_sql:
{% macro postgres__get_relations() -%}

  {#
      -- in pg_depend, objid is the dependent, refobjid is the referenced object
      --  > a pg_depend entry indicates that the referenced object cannot be
      --  > dropped without also dropping the dependent object.
  #}

  {%- call statement('relations', fetch_result=True) -%}
    with relation as (
        select
            pg_rewrite.ev_class as class,
            pg_rewrite.oid as id
        from pg_rewrite
    ),
    class as (
        select
            oid as id,
            relname as name,
            relnamespace as schema,
            relkind as kind
        from pg_class
    ),
    dependency as (
        select distinct
            pg_depend.objid as id,
            pg_depend.refobjid as ref
        from pg_depend
    ),
    schema as (
        select
            pg_namespace.oid as id,
            pg_namespace.nspname as name
        from pg_namespace
        where nspname != 'information_schema' and nspname not like 'pg\_%'
    ),
    referenced as (
        select
            relation.id AS id,
            referenced_class.name ,
            referenced_class.schema ,
            referenced_class.kind
        from relation
        join class as referenced_class on relation.class=referenced_class.id
        where referenced_class.kind in ('r', 'v', 'm')
    ),
    relationships as (
        select
            referenced.name as referenced_name,
            referenced.schema as referenced_schema_id,
            dependent_class.name as dependent_name,
            dependent_class.schema as dependent_schema_id,
            referenced.kind as kind
        from referenced
        join dependency on referenced.id=dependency.id
        join class as dependent_class on dependency.ref=dependent_class.id
        where
            (referenced.name != dependent_class.name or
             referenced.schema != dependent_class.schema)
    )

    select
        referenced_schema.name as referenced_schema,
        relationships.referenced_name as referenced_name,
        dependent_schema.name as dependent_schema,
        relationships.dependent_name as dependent_name
    from relationships
    join schema as dependent_schema on relationships.dependent_schema_id=dependent_schema.id
    join schema as referenced_schema on relationships.referenced_schema_id=referenced_schema.id
    group by referenced_schema, referenced_name, dependent_schema, dependent_name
    order by referenced_schema, referenced_name, dependent_schema, dependent_name;

  {%- endcall -%}

  {{ return(load_result('relations').table) }}
{% endmacro %}

macro.dbt_postgres.postgres__list_relati.name: postgres__list_relations_without_caching
macro.dbt_postgres.postgres__list_relati.macro_sql:
{% macro postgres__list_relations_without_caching(schema_relation) %}
  {% call statement('list_relations_without_caching', fetch_result=True) -%}
    select
      '{{ schema_relation.database }}' as database,
      tablename as name,
      schemaname as schema,
      'table' as type
    from pg_tables
    where schemaname ilike '{{ schema_relation.schema }}'
    union all
    select
      '{{ schema_relation.database }}' as database,
      viewname as name,
      schemaname as schema,
      'view' as type
    from pg_views
    where schemaname ilike '{{ schema_relation.schema }}'
    union all
    select
      '{{ schema_relation.database }}' as database,
      matviewname as name,
      schemaname as schema,
      'materialized_view' as type
    from pg_matviews
    where schemaname ilike '{{ schema_relation.schema }}'
  {% endcall %}
  {{ return(load_result('list_relations_without_caching').table) }}
{% endmacro %}

macro.dbt_postgres.postgres__get_show_in.name: postgres__get_show_indexes_sql
macro.dbt_postgres.postgres__get_show_in.macro_sql:
{% macro postgres__get_show_indexes_sql(relation) %}
    select
        i.relname                                   as name,
        m.amname                                    as method,
        ix.indisunique                              as "unique",
        array_to_string(array_agg(a.attname), ',')  as column_names
    from pg_index ix
    join pg_class i
        on i.oid = ix.indexrelid
    join pg_am m
        on m.oid=i.relam
    join pg_class t
        on t.oid = ix.indrelid
    join pg_namespace n
        on n.oid = t.relnamespace
    join pg_attribute a
        on a.attrelid = t.oid
        and a.attnum = ANY(ix.indkey)
    where t.relname = '{{ relation.identifier }}'
      and n.nspname = '{{ relation.schema }}'
      and t.relkind in ('r', 'm')
    group by 1, 2, 3
    order by 1, 2, 3
{% endmacro %}

doc.dbt.__overview__.name: __overview__
doc.dbt.__overview__.block_contents:
### Welcome!

Welcome to the auto-generated documentation for your dbt project!

### Navigation

You can use the `Project` and `Database` navigation tabs on the left side of the window to explore the models
in your project.

#### Project Tab
The `Project` tab mirrors the directory structure of your dbt project. In this tab, you can see all of the
models defined in your dbt project, as well as models imported from dbt packages.

#### Database Tab
The `Database` tab also exposes your models, but in a format that looks more like a database explorer. This view
shows relations (tables and views) grouped into database schemas. Note that ephemeral models are _not_ shown
in this interface, as they do not exist in the database.

### Graph Exploration
You can click the blue icon on the bottom-right corner of the page to view the lineage graph of your models.

On model pages, you'll see the immediate parents and children of the model you're exploring. By clicking the `Expand`
button at the top-right of this lineage pane, you'll be able to see all of the models that are used to build,
or are built from, the model you're exploring.

Once expanded, you'll be able to use the `--select` and `--exclude` model selection syntax to filter the
models in the graph. For more information on model selection, check out the [dbt docs](https://docs.getdbt.com/docs/model-selection-syntax).

Note that you can also right-click on models to interactively filter and explore the graph.

---

### More information

- [What is dbt](https://docs.getdbt.com/docs/introduction)?
- Read the [dbt viewpoint](https://docs.getdbt.com/docs/viewpoint)
- [Installation](https://docs.getdbt.com/docs/installation)
- Join the [dbt Community](https://www.getdbt.com/community/) for questions and discussion

test.stripe_integration_tests.consistenc.name: consistency_line_item_enhanced
test.stripe_integration_tests.consistenc.raw_code:
{{ config(
    tags="fivetran_validations",
    enabled=var('fivetran_validation_tests_enabled', false) and var('stripe__standardized_billing_model_enabled', false)
) }}

with prod as (
    select *
    except(fee_amount, refund_amount, transaction_type) --remove before merge
    from {{ target.schema }}_stripe_prod.stripe__line_item_enhanced
),

dev as (
    select *
    except(fee_amount, refund_amount, transaction_type) --remove before merge
    from {{ target.schema }}_stripe_dev.stripe__line_item_enhanced
),

prod_not_in_dev as (
    -- rows from prod not found in dev
    select * from prod
    except distinct
    select * from dev
),

dev_not_in_prod as (
    -- rows from dev not found in prod
    select * from dev
    except distinct
    select * from prod
),

final as (
    select
        *,
        'from prod' as source
    from prod_not_in_dev

    union all -- union since we only care if rows are produced

    select
        *,
        'from dev' as source
    from dev_not_in_prod
)

select *
from final

test.stripe_integration_tests.consistenc.name: consistency_customer_overview
test.stripe_integration_tests.consistenc.raw_code:
{{ config(
    tags="fivetran_validations",
    enabled=var('fivetran_validation_tests_enabled', false)
) }}

-- this test ensures the customer_overview end model matches the prior version by comparing the aggregated fields
-- the below iterates through the prod and dev names to reduce redundancy of logic
with
{% for prod_or_dev in ('prod', 'dev') %}
    {% set cols = [
        'total_sales',
        'total_refunds',
        'total_gross_transaction_amount',
        'total_fees',
        'total_net_transaction_amount',
        'total_sales_count',
        'total_refund_count',
        'sales_this_month',
        'refunds_this_month',
        'gross_transaction_amount_this_month',
        'fees_this_month',
        'net_transaction_amount_this_month',
        'sales_count_this_month',
        'refund_count_this_month',
        'total_failed_charge_count',
        'total_failed_charge_amount',
        'failed_charge_count_this_month',
        'failed_charge_amount_this_month'
    ] %}

    {{ prod_or_dev }} as (
        select
            {% for col in cols %}
                {% if not loop.first %}, {% endif %}
                floor(sum({{ col }})) as summed_{{ col }} -- floor and sum is to keep consistency between dev and prod aggs
            {% endfor %}
        from {{ target.schema }}_stripe_{{ prod_or_dev }}.stripe__customer_overview
    ),
{% endfor %}

prod_not_in_dev as (
    -- rows from prod not found in dev
    select * from prod
    except distinct
    select * from dev
),

dev_not_in_prod as (
    -- rows from dev not found in prod
    select * from dev
    except distinct
    select * from prod
),

final as (
    select
        *,
        'from prod' as source
    from prod_not_in_dev

    union all -- union since we only care if rows are produced

    select
        *,
        'from dev' as source
    from dev_not_in_prod
)

select *
from final

test.stripe_integration_tests.consistenc.name: consistency_daily_overview
test.stripe_integration_tests.consistenc.raw_code:
{{ config(
    tags="fivetran_validations",
    enabled=var('fivetran_validation_tests_enabled', false)
) }}

-- this test ensures the daily_overview end model matches the prior version
-- and is aggregated on the date_index grain since the rollings totals will cause variation at the account_id grain
-- the below iterates through the prod and dev names to reduce redudancy of logic
with
{% for prod_or_dev in ('prod', 'dev') %}
    {% set cols = adapter.get_columns_in_relation(ref('stripe__daily_overview')) %}
    {{ prod_or_dev }} as (
        select
            date_index,
            source_relation
            {% for col in cols if col.name not in ["account_id", "account_daily_id", "date_day", "date_week", "date_month", "date_year", "date_index", "source_relation"] %}
                , floor(sum({{ col.name }})) as summed_{{ col.name }} -- floor and sum is to keep consistency between dev and prod aggs
            {% endfor %}
        from {{ target.schema }}_stripe_{{ prod_or_dev }}.stripe__daily_overview
        group by 1,2 -- need to group to remove randomization stemming from rolling totals
    ),
{% endfor %} 

prod_not_in_dev as (
    -- rows from prod not found in dev
    select * from prod
    except distinct
    select * from dev
),

dev_not_in_prod as (
    -- rows from dev not found in prod
    select * from dev
    except distinct
    select * from prod
),

final as (
    select
        *,
        'from prod' as source
    from prod_not_in_dev

    union all -- union since we only care if rows are produced

    select
        *,
        'from dev' as source
    from dev_not_in_prod
)

select *
from final

with prod as (
    select count(*) as prod_rows
    from {{ target.schema }}_stripe_prod.stripe__daily_overview
),

dev as (
    select count(*) as dev_rows
    from {{ target.schema }}_stripe_dev.stripe__daily_overview
)

-- test will return values and fail if the row counts don't match
select *
from prod
join dev
    on prod.prod_rows != dev.dev_rows

    select * from dev
    except distinct
    select * from prod
),

)

with staging_model as (

        invoice_id as header_id,
        count(*) as stg_line_item_count,
    from {{ ref('stg_stripe__invoice_line_item') }}
    group by 1
),

end_model as (
    select 
        header_id,
        count(*) as end_model_count
    from {{ ref('stripe__line_item_enhanced') }}
    group by 1
),

final as (
    select 
        end_model.header_id as end_header_id,
        staging_model.header_id as staging_header_id,
        end_model.end_model_count as end_model_row_count,
        (staging_model.stg_line_item_count + 1) as stg_model_row_count
    from staging_model
    full outer join end_model
        on end_model.header_id = staging_model.header_id
)

from final

Therefore, to avoid this we can relying on the fact that no fanouts (end model has a greater count than staging) are occurring from this integrity test is sufficient.
